&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Case Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Manchester&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hybrid: &lt;/strong&gt;2 days in office, 3 days WFH following a successful probation period&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; Basic salary up to £34k - OTE £47K&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Big things are happening here. We&#39;re entering a new phase of exciting growth, and you could be a key part of it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a talented and motivated Case Manager to join our highly skilled team. As a Case Manager, you will play a crucial role in helping our customers secure their financial needs. You will be responsible for packaging loan applications, guiding customers through the application process, and ensuring a best-in-class experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a real opportunity to join a market-leading financial platform backed by ClearScore’s global success and long-term growth plans. You&#39;ll be working alongside some of the best in the industry, with access to training, support, strong partnerships with top lenders and a clear vision for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, evaluate and package secured loan applications to ensure completeness and accuracy, resulting in the pay out of a case.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify customer information, including income, employment, credit history, and property details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and process loan documents, including loan agreements, disclosures etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough due diligence of a customer’s application and ensure all necessary documentation is obtained.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with lenders, and other relevant parties to resolve any discrepancies or issues that arise during the loan process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaising directly with customers by explaining and completing the application process in accordance with the Aro Money’s Compliance and Training &amp;amp; Competence Procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with customers, keeping them fully informed throughout the process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet or exceed targets and KPIs while maintaining high levels of customer satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with our exceptional team of administrators and advisors to support our customers&#39; applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep up-to-date with industry regulations and lender criteria to provide informed guidance to customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play a key role in Aro’s continuous innovation of best-in-class customer experience by actively suggesting new ideas and processes where approximate and be willing to put these into practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
